title: [ICE]: index out of bounds: the len is 4 but the index is 2147483649 (compiler/rustc_middle/src/mir/mod.rs:471:22)

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
This error occurred in CI so unfortunately I don't have a minimal repro as I can't reproduce it locally. I also wasn't able to reproduce it in CI either: rerunning the job "fixed" the problem. Possibly related to #107582? There's a second panic: thread 'rustc' panicked at 'called `Option::unwrap()` on a `None` value', /rustc/fc594f15669680fa70d255faec3ca3fb507c3405/compiler/rustc_query_system/src/query/plumbing.rs:269:23 ### Code Here's the PR where I experienced it: https://github.com/RustCrypto/elliptic-curves/pull/737 Here's the first commit where it manifested: https://github.com/RustCrypto/elliptic-curves/pull/737/commits/061548d3b0268b7e3eb1772a8cfe6f372d97ca33 ### Meta From CI: note: rustc 1.67.0 (fc594f156 2023-01-24) running on x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu note: compiler flags: --crate-type lib -C opt-level=2 -C embed-bitcode=no -C debuginfo=2 -C debug-assertions=on ### Error output From: https://github.com/RustCrypto/elliptic-curves/actions/runs/4078778175/jobs/7029397528 ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'index out of bounds: the len is 4 but the index is 2147483649', compiler/rustc_middle/src/mir/mod.rs:471:22 ```
